'j. Since all s'i have length L, this means all s'i must be distinct. But there's a catch: if si is a prefix of sj, then s'i will also be a prefix of s'j if we aren't careful. But if they have the same length L, they can only be prefixes if they are equal. The real constraint is: we need to find the minimum L such that we can assign a unique string of length L to each si that starts with si, AND for any i, j, si is not a prefix of sj (unless"
